// SKIP: The accepted answer is a probabilistic expected-damage analysis comparing Vow of Enmity (advantage on attack rolls) against Hexblade's Curse (flat bonus damage + expanded 19–20 crit range). Two fundamental gaps prevent encoding this in the spec: (1) `resolveAttackRoll` only recognises a natural 20 as a critical hit — the 19–20 expanded crit range of Hexblade's Curse cannot be modelled; (2) the crossover-point analysis requires computing expected value over dice probability distributions, but all rolls are pre-resolved concrete integers in the spec, making statistical comparisons (e.g. "advantage reduces miss chance by X%") impossible to express as a single deterministic `assert`.